        public AccessPathTuple simplify()
        Checks whether this tuple is equivalent to one of the simple predefined ones. If so, it returns the shared predefined object. Otherwise, it returns this object.
        Returns:

      • toAccessPath

        public AccessPath toAccessPath​(soot.Value baseVal,
                               InfoflowManager manager,
                               boolean canHaveImmutableAliases)
        Creates an access path from an access path definition object
        Parameters:
        baseVal - The base for the new access path
        manager - The manager to be used for creating new access paths
        canHaveImmutableAliases - Specifies if the newly tainted value can have aliases that are not overwritten by the current operation, i.e., whether there must be an alias analysis from the source statement backwards through the code
        Returns:
        The newly created access path
